        <div class="row py-3 text-muted">

            <p>
                This website is developed using simple MVC razor pages.
                However, this website is powered by <b class="fg-theme">Github Actions</b> and <b class="fg-theme">Azure Kubernetes Service (AKS). </b>
                Behind the scenes AKS is connected with <b class="fg-theme">Azure Container Registry </b> in which image is pushed by Github actions
            </p>
            <p>
                AKS is deployed on a cluster which has two node pools i.e <b class="fg-theme">System Pool and User Pool </b>.
                To keep the cost low each pool has only one node.
            </p>
            <p>
                The authorization between AKS and ACR is handled
                by service principal. But it can also be handled by Azure managed Identies.
            </p>
            <p>
                <b class="fg-theme"> Kubernetes Manifests and Helm charts </b> are created which are deployed using github actions.
                Other than deployment manifest, this website
                is using <b class="fg-theme"> nginx ingress controller. </b> <a href="https://github.com/kapilkhub/kapilkhubchandani"> here is the source code</a>
